page.title: 20CONSERVATION IN BEDFORDSHIRE
page.content: One of the most active organisations working to conserve the countryside in south west Cambridgeshire and Bedfordshire is the{Bedfordshire and {Huntingdonshire Naturalist Trust.}They are responsible for the cutting of a new nature trail in the southern area of the{Wyboston Lakes Leisure Park.}It is hoped that the trail will be completed by September 1985. This small natural area is bounded by the River Great Ouse to the east and farmland close to the village of Wyboston to the west. Existing tracks are being supplemented by new pathways which wind through tall reeds and wooded glades. There is a wide variety of birds and insects to be seen as well as small fish in the streams and river. Grass Snakes and Adders have also been observed.
